      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Preheat your oven to 180°C/350°F/Gas mark 4",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Cream the butter and caster sugar together until the mixture is pale and light. This is easiest using a free-standing mixer and will take about 3-4 minutes on medium speed.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Gradually add the beaten eggs, mixing well between each addition and scraping down the sides of the bowl from time to time. Add the vanilla extract and mix again.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Sift the flour and salt into the bowl and fold in using a large metal spoon or rubber spatula until the mixture is glossy and smooth",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Divide the mixture between the Mini Sandwich Tin (roughly 1 heaped dessertspoon of mixture in each well) and level with a teaspoon.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Bake on the middle shelf of the hot oven for about 15 minutes. The cakes should be golden and well risen. Test with a wooden skewer in the middle of one cake. It should come out clean.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Leave the cakes to rest in the tin for 2 minutes and then carefully ease out onto a wire cooling rack and leave until cold.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "To make the buttercream, cream together the butter, icing sugar and vanilla extract until the mixture is pale and light.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Cut each of the cakes in half and spread the bottom layer with buttercream. Top with a teaspoon of jam and sandwich with the top cake layer. Lightly dust with icing sugar to serve.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Test with a skewer. It should come out with a few moist crumbs, not wet batter. Don't open the oven before three-quarters of the bake time.",
              "cause": "Underbaked, or the oven door opened too early.",
              "symptom": "Cake sinks in the middle"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Check at the minimum bake time and every five minutes after. Weigh flour for cake recipes, cup measures vary by 20% depending on how you scoop.",
              "cause": "Overbaked, or too much flour measured by cup not weight.",
              "symptom": "Cake is dry"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Drop the temperature by 10°C and check earlier. Domed cakes can be trimmed flat once cool.",
              "cause": "Oven too hot, or batter too thick.",
              "symptom": "Top cracked or domed"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Check baking powder is fresh. It loses lift after six months. Use room-temperature butter and eggs so the batter holds air.",
              "cause": "Raising agent stale or omitted, or butter and eggs cold.",
              "symptom": "Cake didn't rise"
            }
          ],
          "heading": "If something goes wrong"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Variations",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Citrus version: replace the vanilla with the zest of an orange or lemon.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Nut-free: swap ground almonds for desiccated coconut or extra plain flour, weight for weight.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Best fresh. Leftovers keep two days in the fridge; reheat covered with a splash of liquid.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A British home cook's dish. It sits among the recipes families remember without thinking about, the kind that gets adjusted across generations and never quite the same twice.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
